commit.message:
Add an intrinsic for named barrier arrive/signal operation

.

Fixed warning from static code analyser

.

Create a class for SEV management

All the SEV-related methods and data were declared static and
outside of any class. It lead to issues with map objects. Now
everything is collected to a single class which instance is
created for every module being processed

Add support for XeHPCVG platform

.

Add support for Arrow Lake and Lunar Lake devices (#201)

.

commit.message:
Removed deprecated API usage since LLVM 18

This can be done safely because the used APIs are always return ture (since LLVM 18).

Fixed upstream pulldown build error

Fixed build failure related to upstream changes

Fixed warning from static code analyser

.

Replace old kernel with rewritten kernel in metadata only since LLVM 17

This can be done safely (will not cause type mismatch) when only opaque pointers are used (since LLVM 17).

Replace all uses before removing function

There might be module level named metadata referencing old function,
so we have to replace all uses before removing old function.

Prevent creation of scalable vectors

To create a vector IITDescriptor::getVector() should be called with isScalable arg explicitly set to false

Fix pointer sev-rich form issue

While creating a SEV from a pointer a bitcast instruction should be used
ONLY when the result is also a pointer. Otherwise we can face the
following sequence:
%v = bitcast T* to <1 x T*>
%s = extractlement <1 x T*> %v, <i32> %zero_idx
%e = some_user_of_T <T*> %s

The excessive ExtractElement instruction cannot be removed since llvm
SimplifyExtractElementInst does not support such pattern.

Disable some LITs for llvm-17 and llvm-18

Typed pointer support was removed starting with llvm-17

Fix llvm-17 build

.

Fixed warning from statical code analizer

Fixed high-priority waring in GenXCisaBuilder and GenXArgIndirection

Guard removed typed pointer enum within version macro

Community has removed these typed pointer enum, guard them within
version macro to fix build error.

Remove llvm-version dependence from interface file

.

Mark llvm15 tests failures

.

Get rid of llvm::Optional usages

Fix build after
https://reviews.llvm.org/D149128

Mark new lsc_load_merge intrinsics as LSC ones

.

Mark address convert intrinsic with VCFunction attribute

.

Fix cast handling in GenXSPIRVReaderAdaptor (2nd attempt)

.

Fix cast instructions handling in GenXSPIRVReaderAdaptor

.

Fix build against llvm-14 and llvm-15

.

Fix build against llvm-14 and llvm-15

.

Use target extension types for SPIR-V opaque arguments

Match SPIR-V translator change to support opaque pointers on frontend:
https://github.com/KhronosGroup/SPIRV-LLVM-Translator/pull/1799

Avoid non-generic address space cast instructions

Some frontends mix private and global pointers which is not allowed by
SPIR-V. Using ptr->i64->ptr cast in this case to avoid failures until
the frontends are fixed.

Get rid of genx.address.convert intrinsic calls

.

Fix attributes for llvm-16

---------------------------

Adding SECURITY.md file
